32 and 64-bit Linux "Hello World!" programs, written in NASM.


-----------------
-   Tutorials   -
-----------------

32-bit tutorial:
http://blog.markloiseau.com/2012/04/hello-world-nasm-linux/

64-bit tutorial:
http://blog.markloiseau.com/2012/05/64-bit-hello-world-in-linux-assembly-nasm/


-----------------
- Prerequisites -
-----------------

NASM: http://www.nasm.us/
gcc or ld: http://packages.ubuntu.com/search?keywords=build-essential

To install on Ubuntu:
$ sudo apt-get install nasm build-essential


-----------------
-   Compiling   -
-----------------

To compile everything, enter the directory containing the Makefile and the NASM sources
and type "make"

To compile just the tiny executables or just the normal executables, type "make tiny" or "make normal" respectively.

To delete all of the compiled object files and executables, leaving only the original source files, type "make clean"


------------------
- Checking size  -
------------------

Use wordcount (wc):

$ wc hello32
  1   6 956 hello32

$ wc hello64
  1   6 980 hello64

